<p>GDP growth: 1.1% GDP: $66bn (PPP: $83bn) Inflation: 2.4% Population: 4.5m GDP per head: $14,760 (PPP: $18,550)</p>

<p>The centre-left will return to power in 2012 after more than a decade, replacing a centre-right coalition ejected amid austerity and street protests. Despite public disaffection with the policies of the outgoing administration, the new one will do little different, mainly because the parlous state of the economy leaves few options. The foreign debt is high, as is the public deficit, and growth prospects are modest, so the focus will remain firmly on austerity and structural reforms, many of them mandated by the EU as a condition of entry.</p>

